.TH btctax-reconcile-reclassify-outflow 1  btctax "btctax manual"
.SH NAME
reclassify\-outflow \- Reclassify a pending TransferOut
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBreclassify\-outflow\fR <\fB\-\-as\-kind\fR> <\fB\-\-amount\fR> [\fB\-\-fee\fR] [\fB\-\-appraisal\fR] [\fB\-\-donee\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIOUT\fR> 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Reclassify a pending TransferOut
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-as\-kind\fR \fI<AS_KIND>\fR

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
sell
.IP \(bu 2
spend
.IP \(bu 2
gift
.IP \(bu 2
donate
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-amount\fR \fI<AMOUNT>\fR
USD fair\-market value of the disposed BTC at the transfer date — dollars, NOT sats. For a sell/spend this is the gross proceeds; for a gift/donation it is the FMV at the contribution date (26 CFR 1.170A\-1(c)(2)). Entering the sats amount here is a common error and draws a non\-fatal warning when it exceeds 100x the market value
.TP
\fB\-\-fee\fR \fI<FEE>\fR

.TP
\fB\-\-appraisal\fR

.TP
\fB\-\-donee\fR \fI<DONEE>\fR
Free\-form donee identifier (e.g. "Alice", "Charity X"). Carried through to removals.csv and Form 8283; does not affect tax math
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
<\fIOUT\fR>

